{"url": "https://www.slo.courts.ca.gov/gi/court-reporter-protem.htm", "_type": "index", "body": ["<p>When agreeing to work as an Official Reporter Pro Tempore for San Luis Obispo Superior Court, each Official Reporter Pro Tempore confirms and agrees:\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>to maintain a valid, current California Certified Shorthand Reporter License and maintain current contact information with the Court as directed by the Supervising Court Reporter;</li>\n\t<li>that appearance fees, including real-time fees, are the responsibility of the party or parties who arranged the reporter services, and will not be charged to the Court;</li>\n\t<li>to comply with the statutes and rules applicable to Official Reporters Pro Tempore, including the duty to timely prepare transcripts in the proper appellate form;</li>\n\t<li>to leave reporting notes or an electronic copy with the Court as directed by the Supervising Court Reporter;</li>\n\t<li>to follow directions from the Court, and to be subject to the jurisdiction of the Court to the same extent as an Official Reporter;</li>\n\t<li>to be available for reading of notes back to the jury if serving during a jury trial.<br/>\n\t&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>\n\n<strong>Daily Procedures Prior to Reporting</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Check in with Courtroom Clerk and provide name, CSR License Number, contact information, including what agency, if any, you are working for so you may be noticed in the event of an appeal</li>\n\t<li>Sign the Reporter Calendar located at the reporter desk in the courtroom well</li>\n\t<li>Provide your raw notes electronically to the Court Reporter Supervisor.</li>\n\t<li>Contact our Fiscal Department at (805) 781-5675 and provide all vendor information necessary to receive payment of transcripts</li>\n\t<li>Electronic Deposit is available for payment of transcripts</li>\n\t<li>Direct any questions to the Court Reporter Supervisor via email or phone: 805-781-1132</li>\n\t<li>Free WiFi is available: SLO-PUBLIC<br/>\n\t&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>Court Reporter Requirements</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Comply with the statutes and rules applicable to Official Reporter Pro Tempore</li>\n\t<li>Transcribe and prepare in proper form all transcript requests, including appeals, in a timely manner</li>\n\t<li>Be available for read back of notes</li>\n\t<li>Supply an electronic copy of the notes to the Court for archival purposes</li>\n\t<li>Maintain current contact information with the Court</li>\n\t<li>All fees for reporting services will be the responsibility of the party(ies) and will not be charged to the Court<br/>\n\t&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>Transcripts</strong>\n\n<p>Transcripts produced by an official reporter pro tempore will be treated, for court purposes, identically with transcripts prepared by official reporters.&nbsp; Reporting notes of an official reporter pro tempore are official records of the Court., per Government Code Section 69955(a).&nbsp; The notes of official reporters pro tempore, when transcribed and certified, are prima facie evidence of the testimony and proceedings, per Code of Civil Procedure Section 273(a).<br/>\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<strong>Appeal Procedures</strong>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Upon receipt of an appeal notice, immediately read entire notice to confirm the dates you\u2019ve been noticed and whether the appeal will be in hard copy form or electronic form</li>\n\t<li>Notify by \"reply all\" whether or not the dates noticed are correct, and whether the transcripts have been previously prepared or not</li>\n\t<li>Utilize the Lead Reporter Sheet to confirm your volumes and blocked page numbers</li>\n\t<li>Waiver of Deposit is an option, if requested, (CRC Rule8.130(b)(3)(A)) in lieu of the parties following CRC Rule 8.130(b)(1)(B)(i) &amp; (ii)</li>\n\t<li>Follow the California Rules of Court Rule 8.144 for Reporter\u2019s appeal transcript guidelines</li>\n\t<li>When preparing the Transcript Invoice for your appeal, be sure to follow California Government Code Section 69950</li>\n\t<li>Include a <strong>copy</strong> of your Transcript Invoice with your completed appeal transcript to the appeals clerk</li>\n\t<li>Provide your \"Original\" transcript invoice to the Supervising Court Reporter for payment. (Any invoices not following Section 69950 of the Government Code will be returned for correction)</li>\n</ul></p>"], "_template": "5a0b-4d51-805f", "parent": ["https://www.slo.courts.ca.gov/gi/court-reporter.htm"], "title": ["Pro Tem Reporter Procedures"]}
{"url": "https://www.slo.courts.ca.gov/gi/job-descriptions.htm", "_type": "index", "body": ["<p><strong>Job Class and Salary Listing</strong>\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<strong>A</strong>\n\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Account Clerk/Senior Account Clerk</li>\n\t<li>Accountant I/II</li>\n\t<li>Accounting Technician</li>\n\t<li>Administrative Analyst</li>\n\t<li>Automation Analyst I/II</li>\n\t<li>Automation Specialist I/II/III</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>B</strong>\n\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\tBusiness Systems Analyst\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>C</strong>\n\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Commissioner</li>\n\t<li>Court Executive Officer&nbsp;</li>\n\t<li>Court Interpreter</li>\n\t<li>Court Reporter</li>\n\t<li>Courtroom Clerk I/II</li>\n\t<li>Courtroom Clerk III</li>\n\t<li>Courtroom Operations Supervisor</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>D</strong>\n\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Department Manager</li>\n\t<li>Director of Civil Operations</li>\n\t<li>Director of Courtroom Operation</li>\n\t<li>Director of Human Resources</li>\n\t<li>Director of Information Technology</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>F</strong>\n\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Facilities Manager</li>\n\t<li>Family Court Services Mediator I/II</li>\n\t<li>Family Law Facilitator II</li>\n\t<li>Fiscal Analyst</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n\n\n<strong>H</strong>\n\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Human Resources&nbsp;Specialist</li>\n\t<li>Human Resources Analyst</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>I</strong>\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Infrastructure Analyst</li>\n\t<li>Intern</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>L</strong>\n\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Legal Process Clerk Trainee I/II</li>\n\t<li>Legal Process Clerk III</li>\n\t<li>Legal Process Supervisor</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>N</strong>\n\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Network Administrator</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>P</strong>\n\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Probate Investigator</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>R</strong>\n\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Research Attorney&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>S</strong>\n\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Secretary I/II</li>\n\t<li>Self-Help Legal Assistant</li>\n\t<li>Self-Help Legal Clerk</li>\n\t<li>Senior Fiscal and Administrative Services Director</li>\n\t<li>Senior Secretary </li>\n\t<li>Supervising Court Reporter</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n</p>"], "_template": "5a0b-4d51-805f", "parent": ["https://www.slo.courts.ca.gov/gi/employment.htm"], "title": ["Salary Lisiting and Job Specifications"]}
{"url": "https://www.slo.courts.ca.gov/gi/benefits.htm", "_type": "index", "body": ["<p>Personnel Policies and Procedures\n\n<strong>Interpreter Unit (Unit 17)</strong>\n\n<p><strong>Job Titles</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Court Interpreter</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About Unit &amp; Benefits</strong><br/>\nMemorandum of Understanding<br/>\nBenefits at a Glance</p>\n\n<strong>Technical Unit (Unit 18)</strong>\n\n<p><strong>Job Titles</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Automation Specialist I, II, III</li>\n\t<li>Court Reporter</li>\n\t<li>Probate Investigator</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About Unit &amp; Benefits</strong><br/>\nMemorandum of Understanding<br/>\nBenefits at a Glance</p>\n\n<strong>Supervisory Unit (Unit 19)</strong>\n\n<p><strong>Job Titles</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Courtroom Operations Supervisor</li>\n\t<li>Legal Proces&nbsp;Supervisor</li>\n\t<li>Supervising Court Reporter</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About Unit &amp; Benefits</strong><br/>\nMemorandum of Understanding <br/>\nBenefits at a Glance</p>\n\n<strong>Miscellaneous Unit (Unit 20)</strong>\n\n<p><strong>Job Titles</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Account Clerk/Senior Account Clerk</li>\n\t<li>Accounting Technician</li>\n\t<li>Courtroom Clerk I/II</li>\n\t<li>Courtroom Clerk III</li>\n\t<li>Legal Process Clerk Trainee I/II</li>\n\t<li>Legal Process Clerk III</li>\n\t<li>Secretary I/II</li>\n\t<li>Self Help Legal Assistant</li>\n\t<li>Self Help Legal Clerk</li>\n\t<li>Senior Secretary</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About Unit &amp; Benefits</strong><br/>\nMemorandum of Understanding<br/>\nBenefits at a Glance</p>\n\n<strong>Unit&nbsp;24</strong>\n\n<p><strong>Job Titles</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Court Executive Officer</li>\n\t<li>Department Manager</li>\n\t<li>Director of Civil Operations</li>\n\t<li>Director of Courtroom Operations</li>\n\t<li>Director of Human Resources</li>\n\t<li>Director of Information Technology</li>\n\t<li>Facilities Manager</li>\n\t<li>Family Law Facilitator</li>\n\t<li>Research Attorney</li>\n\t<li>Senior Fiscal and Administrative Services Director</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About Benefits</strong><br/>\nBenefits at a Glance</p>\n\n<strong>Unit 25</strong>\n\n<p><strong>Job Titles</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Commissioner</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About Benefits</strong><br/>\nBenefits at a Glance</p>\n\n<strong>Unit&nbsp;26</strong>\n\n<p><strong>Job Titles</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Administrative Analyst \u2013 Confidential</li>\n\t<li>Fiscal Analyst \u2013 Confidential</li>\n\t<li>Human Resources Analyst \u2013 Confidential</li>\n\t<li>Human Resources Specialist \u2013 Confidential</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About Benefits</strong><br/>\nBenefits at a Glance</p>\n\n<strong>Unit 27</strong>\n\n<p><strong>Job Titles</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Accountant I/II</li>\n\t<li>Automation Analyst I/II</li>\n\t<li>Business Systems Analyst</li>\n\t<li>Family Court Services Mediator</li>\n\t<li>Infrastructure Analyst</li>\n\t<li>Network Administrator</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>About Benefits&nbsp;</strong><br/>\nBenefits at a Glance</p></p>"], "_template": "5a0b-4d51-805f", "parent": ["https://www.slo.courts.ca.gov/gi/employment.htm"], "title": ["Benefits / MOUs / Personnel Policies"]}
